	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.65]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Blessed Faydark Thunderbolt: Dmg 30, Dly 38. Range 250. Wt 3.00. +5 Str, +5 Agi, +5 Dex, +5 Wis, +10 vsMg, +10 vsFire, +10 vsCold, +50 HP, +50 Mana, MAGIC&nbsp;&nbsp; Classes: Ra P Ro Wr. All Races. <br><br>Recurved Wormwood Bow: Dmg 32, Dly 29. Range 220. Wt 3.50. +10 AC, +10 Dex, +15 Int, +10 Cha, +15 vsMg, +5 vsPos, +5 vsDis, +75 HP, +75 Mana, LORE MAGIC NODROP   Classes: Wr Ro Sk P Ra. All Races.<br><br>Its a tough call.  I would really hate to lose the 5 wis and the saves for fire and cold - but the Plus poison and disease is much harder to get tho.<br><br>As I have made a nightmare bow for every Archer capable player in my guild - So it makes deciding who gets a bow pretty easy - we already know what bow everyone has.  When we take the event that drops this bow - and it if it does - I think I will call the MT warrior to loot overr me - even tho the Dmg / Delay ratio would be more devestating on me.   The funny thing is that this bow is designed for a shadowknight with the int on it over wis.   <br><br>Honsestly who gets to loot this depends on how your guild treats archery/ stat slots.  The Hit points alone would make me prefer it goes to a MT class over the ranger that can use it for devastating DPS with bow shots<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Ranger Serano<br><a href="http://www.tribalfury.com" target=_new>http://www.tribalfury.com</a></td></tr>
